# A spread made from cold [[tea]] and [[brown sugar]].
#: 1977: ''Even the basic damper mixture could be treated in all sorts of different ways &ndash; mixed with dried fruit, spread with cold tea and brown sugar (a concoction known as Murrumbidge jam), or cooked on top of a stew to form a pie crust.'' &mdash; Richard Daunton-Fear and Penelope Vigar, ''Australian Colonial Cookery'', Rigby, 1977, ISBN 0-7270-0187-6 (discussing 19th century cookery)
